M|mia|**Shared floor rules (apply to all ventures, from `docs/mem/design.md`):**
M|mia|- Minimum 12px / font-weight 800 for any readable text
M|mia|- No hardcoded hex values ÔÇö CSS variable tokens from `globals.css` only
M|mia|- `globals.css` Ôåö `tailwind.config.ts` must stay in sync
M|mia|- No dark overlay on top of any background image
M|mia|- Light containers ÔåÆ dark text. Dark containers ÔåÆ light text. Never swap.
M|mia|**YVON dashboard glass system (canonical reference):**
M|mia|- 4 variants: G1 Clear Ice ┬À G2 Azure Tint ┬À G3 Obsidian ┬À G4 Prism
M|mia|- Exact constants: `app/screens/ceo-command-dashboard/_overview.tsx`
M|mia|- Full spec: `docs/ventures/yvon-dashboard/DESIGN.md`
M|mia|**Rule:** If a token doesn't exist in `globals.css`, add it there first, then use it. Never inline a new color.
M|mia|- vtr ctx always visible ÔÇö `VentureSwitcher` in top nav, persistent
M|mia|- KPI tiles at the top of every data page ÔÇö numbers first, labels below
M|mia|- Max 2 primary CTAs per screen ÔÇö avoid dec paralysis
M|mia|- agt pages: avatar + role + model badge visible at top before any chat input
M|mia|- War Room: show routing chain (`RoutingChain` component) so user sees which specialists were consulted
M|mia|- Inbox: unread count badge on NavBar link; most recent brief at top
M|mia|- **Never hardcode colors** ÔÇö always use CSS variable tokens from `globals.css`. No exceptions.
M|mia|- **Never add new font weights or external font families** without Dev ap
M|mia|- **Never design UI that requires hardcoded colors** ÔÇö always reference design token names
M|mia|- Mark components `'use client'` only when they use hooks, browser APIs, or event handlers
M|mia|- Use server components for data fetching and static UI
M|mia|- No unnecessary `useEffect` ÔÇö prefer RSC data fetching or `useSWR`
M|mia|- All components must be responsive (mobile-first)
M|mia|- Always include ARIA labels on interactive elements
M|mia|- Consume active vtr from cookie `yvon_active_venture` via `vtr-ctx.ts`
M|mia|- `AgentAvatar` component: 3 sizes (`sm`, `md`, `lg`) ÔÇö do not create new sizes
M|mia|If `globals.css` CSS variables are modified, `tailwind.config.ts` must be updated to match immediately. Both must stay in sync ÔÇö verify both files after any color system change.
M|mia|For UX/design tasks: deliver layout descriptions with spacing rules, component specs, interaction notes ÔÇö then implement directly. No handoff needed (Leo no longer separate).
M|mia|When a fix is ready to ship:
M|mia|1. Present ONE brief: "Ready to deploy ÔÇö [what's changing in 1 line]. Commit + push to prod + run migrations if needed. Go?"
M|mia|2. Wait for ap
M|mia|3. Execute fully: `git add [files]` ÔåÆ `git commit` ÔåÆ `git push` ÔåÆ `npm run db:migrate` (if migrations changed)
M|mia|4. Report result
M|mia|Never re-ask mid-dpl. Owner is not always present ÔÇö autonomous deploy on ap is the expected behaviour.
M|mia|Destructive operations (DROP TABLE, data deletion, force-push) still require explicit confirmation regardless.